<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910124-0169</DOCNO><DOCID>910124-0169.</DOCID><HL>   American Shipping Bureau   Reports Istanbul Bombing</HL><DATE>01/24/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><IN>MARINE TRANSPORTATION (MAR)</IN><LP>   PARAMUS, N.J. -- American Bureau of Shipping said itsoffice in Istanbul, Turkey, was bombed yesterday, causingsome damage but no injuries to employees.   The organization said the blast appeared to be a protestagainst U.S. military action in the Gulf. &quot;We can onlysurmise the attack occurred because we are an Americanorganization,&quot; a spokesman said.</LP><TEXT>   The blast broke glass and damaged bookcases and wallpaintings. Before setting off the bomb at about 9 a.m.Istanbul time, the attackers forced the four ABS employees,all Turkish nationals, into a back room, where they escapedthe blast.   ABS is an international classification society thatdetermines the mechanical and structural fitness of ships andmarine facilities.</TEXT></DOC>